If you forgot the root password of SQL, you can remove it from your mac, and reinstall it, and remember the temperory root password.
The step is simple
just type "open -a Finder /usr/local" and then delete all the SQL related folder

======================================
After installation
======================================
How to add MySQL to $PATH variable:
cd to your home folder
$ open -t .bash_profile
Try adding the following line to your .bash_profile file.
export PATH=${PATH}:/usr/local/mysql/bin/

Setting the MySQL root user password on OS X
$ mysql -u root -p
mysql$ ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'MyNewPass'; 
